From a10f6ade5a5335720893ddfe1dbc42c86be53fd6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reardonia <2925104+reardonia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 16:50:55 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 02/18] RendererDRMPRIMEGLES: honor videoscreen.limitedrange
 via per-plane EGL import

The OES_EGL_image_external sampler used today imports a DRMPRIME buffer
as a single multi-plane GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL_OES; Mesa hardcodes the
YUV->RGB matrix in nir_lower_tex.c to always emit full-range RGB
regardless of source range. As a result, videoscreen.limitedrange=true
was silently ignored for video pixels on this renderer, while the GUI
shader chain honored the setting -- producing a range mismatch in the
scanout BO whenever both were composited. Applies to all content
(8-bit SDR and 10-bit HDR alike).

Add a second render path that imports the DRMPRIME dma-buf as separate
per-plane GL_TEXTURE_2D textures and runs them through the standard
BaseYUV2RGBGLSLShader -- the same shader CLinuxRendererGLES uses. The
shader binding, matrix wiring (SetColParams + SetMatrices from the
glMatrixProject/glMatrixModview stack), and vertex attribute layout
are taken directly from CLinuxRendererGLES::RenderSinglePass
(LinuxRendererGLES.cpp:1100-1183). The path is selected per-frame on
UseLimitedColor(), so toggling the setting at runtime switches paths
on the next frame with no shader rebuild.

The only piece without a LinuxRendererGLES analog is the per-plane
EGL import shape itself (LinuxRendererGLES uploads from CPU memory
via glTexImage2D, not EGL). For that one piece the import sequence
is borrowed from CVaapi2Texture::Map (VaapiEGL.cpp:438-560), the only
existing per-plane dma-buf EGL import in the tree.

The OES path remains for full-range output and as the fallback for
source fourccs we don't per-plane-import. Supported formats for the
new path: NV12, P010, P012, P016 (2-plane via SHADER_NV12_RRG);
YUV420 (+10/12/16 bit) (3-plane via SHADER_YV12_10 -- a misnomer for the
per-plane single-channel sampling pattern, see @todo in Configure).

New class CDRMPRIMETextureYUV in DRMPRIMEEGL.{h,cpp} owns the
per-plane EGL import lifecycle.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
